---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const title = "ARBE Monetary Network";
const description =
  "A sovereign, algorithmic, resource-based monetary system aligned with real resources, social justice, and ecological limits.";
---

<BaseLayout {title} {description}>
  {/* Hero */}
  <section class="arbe-page min-h-[70vh] flex items-center px-6 py-16 sm:px-10 lg:px-20">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto grid gap-12 lg:grid-cols-[minmax(0,3fr)_minmax(0,2fr)] items-center">
      <div>
        <span class="inline-block text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.18em] uppercase text-[var(--arbe-teal)] mb-4">
          AMN / ARBE • Monetary Redesign
        </span>
        <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-semibold text-[var(--arbe-blue)] mb-6">
          From debt-money to a transparent, fair, and stable medium of exchange.
        </h1>
        <p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-[var(--arbe-dark)] mb-6 max-w-2xl">
          The purpose of the <strong>Algorithmic Monetary Network (AMN)</strong> and the
          <strong> ARBE currency</strong> is to transform money from an instrument of debt,
          inequality, and control into what it should have always been: a transparent,
          predictable, and stable way to exchange work and coordinate real resources.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-[var(--arbe-dark)]/80 mb-8 max-w-2xl">
          Today&apos;s monetary creation model is structurally misaligned with the common good.
          It is driven by private credit expansion instead of real productive capacity,
          ecological limits, or the long-term well-being of society.
        </p>

        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
          <a
            href="#problems"
            class="btn btn-primary"
          >
            Why the current system fails
          </a>
          <a
            href="#technology"
            class="btn btn-teal"
          >
            The ARBE technological paradigm
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card shadow-sm border border-slate-200/70 bg-[var(--arbe-gray)]">
        <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-[var(--arbe-teal)] mb-2">
          At a glance
        </h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-[var(--arbe-dark)] mb-4">
          ARBE is a <strong>sovereign, digital, algorithmic currency</strong> whose issuance
          is tied to measurable real-world variables:
        </p>
        <ul class="text-sm space-y-1 text-[var(--arbe-dark)]">
          <li>• Renewable energy availability and capacity</li>
          <li>• Sustainable productive output and logistics</li>
          <li>• Territorial resources and ecological limits</li>
          <li>• Social and constitutional objectives (equality, cohesion, sovereignty)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* Section: Systemic problems of debt-based money */}
  <section
    id="problems"
    class="px-6 py-16 sm:px-10 lg:px-20 bg-white border-y border-slate-100"
  >
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <header class="max-w-3xl mb-10">
        <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-semibold text-[var(--arbe-blue)] mb-4">
          What is structurally wrong with the current monetary creation model?
        </h2>
        <p class="text-base text-[var(--arbe-dark)]/85">
          In most contemporary economies, money is created almost entirely through private
          bank credit. This design systematically amplifies inequality, instability, and
          ecological damage instead of correcting them.
        </p>
      </header>

      <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
        {/* Inequality & poverty */}
        <article class="card h-full">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--arbe-blue)] mb-2">
            1. Extreme inequality & structural poverty
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--arbe-dark)] mb-3">
            Credit-based issuance primarily benefits those who already own assets, collateral,
            and privileged access to finance. This leads to:
          </p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-[var(--arbe-dark)] space-y-1">
            <li>• Growing wealth concentration in upper strata</li>
            <li>• Financial exclusion of large segments of the population</li>
            <li>• Persistent increases in inequality indicators</li>
            <li>• Territorial and generational gaps becoming permanent</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        {/* Debt & inflation */}
        <article class="card h-full">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--arbe-blue)] mb-2">
            2. Perpetual debt & chronic inflation
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--arbe-dark)] mb-3">
            Since almost all money is born as bank debt:
          </p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-[var(--arbe-dark)] space-y-1">
            <li>• Every monetary unit carries debt from the moment it is created</li>
            <li>• The system requires constant re-indebtedness to avoid contraction</li>
            <li>• Households, companies, and States are locked into long-term debt cycles</li>
            <li>• Inflation becomes structural, eroding wages and savings over time</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        {/* Economic slavery & misaligned incentives */}
        <article class="card h-full">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--arbe-blue)] mb-2">
            3. Modern economic servitude & misaligned incentives
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--arbe-dark)] mb-3">
            To access basic goods like housing, education, or healthcare, citizens must often
            chain decades of their life to debt repayment. The system:
          </p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-[var(--arbe-dark)] space-y-1">
            <li>• Converts human time and work into streams of interest payments</li>
            <li>• Prioritizes financial returns over social well-being</li>
            <li>• Rewards speculation over real production and innovation</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        {/* Ecology, resources & geopolitics */}
        <article class="card h-full">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--arbe-blue)] mb-2">
            4. Ecological destruction & geopolitical dependence
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--arbe-dark)] mb-3">
            A credit-driven growth paradigm pushes:
          </p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-[var(--arbe-dark)] space-y-1">
            <li>• Unlimited extraction of natural resources</li>
            <li>• Systematic externalization of environmental costs</li>
            <li>• Competition and conflict over scarce strategic resources</li>
            <li>• Dependence on foreign payment and settlement infrastructures (e.g. SWIFT)</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-10 text-sm text-[var(--arbe-dark)]/80 max-w-3xl">
        <p class="mb-3">
          These dynamics generate an environment of recurring bubbles, cycles of inflation
          and deflation, speculative pressure on essential goods (food, water, housing,
          healthcare), and the erosion of a State&apos;s ability to plan its own economy
          and protect the public interest.
        </p>
        <p>
          ARBE is designed as a scientific, rule-based alternative: a monetary system that
          aligns issuance with real resources, social cohesion, and ecological boundaries.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-8">
        <a href="/problems" class="text-sm font-semibold text-[var(--arbe-teal)] underline-offset-4 hover:underline">
          Read the full systemic problem analysis →
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* Section: Technology & new paradigm */}
  <section
    id="technology"
    class="px-6 py-16 sm:px-10 lg:px-20 bg-[var(--arbe-gray)]"
  >
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <header class="max-w-3xl mb-10">
        <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-semibold text-[var(--arbe-blue)] mb-4">
          The available technology enables a new monetary paradigm.
        </h2>
        <p class="text-base text-[var(--arbe-dark)]/85">
          For the first time in history, digital infrastructure, cryptography, sensing,
          and control theory allow us to design a <strong>scientific monetary system</strong>,
          governed by objective rules rather than discretionary decisions or private interests.
        </p>
      </header>

      <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
        <article class="card h-full">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--arbe-blue)] mb-2">
            Real-time economic & energy sensing
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--arbe-dark)] mb-3">
            The digitalization of critical infrastructure (energy, water, logistics,
            transport, agriculture, industry) enables:
          </p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-[var(--arbe-dark)] space-y-1">
            <li>• Measuring productive capacity in real time</li>
            <li>• Tracking resource levels and availability</li>
            <li>• Linking monetary issuance to physical, observable variables</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="card h-full">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--arbe-blue)] mb-2">
            Control theory & automatic regulation
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--arbe-dark)] mb-3">
            Monetary policy can be implemented as an <strong>algorithmic controller</strong>
            that:
          </p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-[var(--arbe-dark)] space-y-1">
            <li>• Detects deviations and imbalances</li>
            <li>• Adjusts issuance and destruction of money automatically</li>
            <li>• Prevents overheating and deep recessions</li>
            <li>• Remains independent from political and electoral cycles</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="card h-full">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--arbe-blue)] mb-2">
            Cryptography, auditability & sovereign ledgers
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--arbe-dark)] mb-3">
            Modern cryptography and distributed ledgers allow:
          </p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-[var(--arbe-dark)] space-y-1">
            <li>• Immutable recording of all monetary operations</li>
            <li>• Real-time public and institutional auditing</li>
            <li>• Protection against political or private manipulation</li>
            <li>• Operation of sovereign payment networks independent of SWIFT and foreign rails</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="card h-full">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--arbe-blue)] mb-2">
            Algorithmic intelligence & constitutional alignment
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--arbe-dark)] mb-3">
            ARBE embeds constitutional and ecological principles directly into its
            monetary rules:
          </p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-[var(--arbe-dark)] space-y-1">
            <li>• Equality, social justice, and territorial cohesion</li>
            <li>• Ecological sustainability and resource preservation</li>
            <li>• National sovereignty and resilience</li>
            <li>• Continuous adjustment based on predictive models and real data</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-10 max-w-3xl text-sm text-[var(--arbe-dark)]/85">
        <p class="mb-3">
          Under this framework, the money supply no longer expands based on private credit
          and speculative expectations, but according to:
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-1">
          <li>• Available renewable energy</li>
          <li>• Sustainable productive capacity</li>
          <li>• Quantified territorial resources</li>
          <li>• The country&apos;s efficiency and social objectives</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* Section: Towards a sovereign digital currency */}
  <section class="px-6 py-16 sm:px-10 lg:px-20 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto card">
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-semibold text-[var(--arbe-blue)] mb-4">
        Towards a sovereign, audit-able digital currency.
      </h2>
      <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-[var(--arbe-dark)] mb-3">
        Building on the above diagnosis and the technological capabilities now available,
        the AMN/ARBE framework proposes a <strong>new monetary constitutional order</strong>
        in which:
      </p>
      <ul class="text-sm sm:text-base text-[var(--arbe-dark)] space-y-1 mb-4">
        <li>• A new sovereign digital currency is created and managed algorithmically.</li>
        <li>• A national payment infrastructure operates independently from foreign systems.</li>
        <li>• Rules for the creation and destruction of money are explicit, auditable, and transparent.</li>
        <li>• Continuous public oversight and real-time auditing are mandatory.</li>
        <li>• The economy gradually transitions towards a resource-based, digitally quantified model.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-[var(--arbe-dark)]">
        ARBE is not just another digital token. It is a proposal to redesign the
        <strong>foundations of money</strong> so that monetary creation serves society,
        the ecosystem, and future generations — instead of subordinating them to
        speculative finance.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <a
          href="/whitepaper"
          class="btn btn-primary"
        >
          Read the full AMN / ARBE Whitepaper
        </a>
        <a
          href="/architecture"
          class="btn btn-teal"
        >
          Explore the technical architecture
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>


